{{Infobox organization | name = Angelic Organics | image = File:Angelic Organics Logo-web.png | image_size = 200px | motto = | formation = {{start date|1990|df=y}} | founder = Farmer John Peterson | founding_location = [[Caledonia, Illinois]], USA | coords = {{coord|42.4538889|-88.9108333|format=dms|display=title|type:landmark_region:US-IL}} | services = [[Community supported agriculture]] | products = Vegetables and Herbs | methods = [[Organic and Biodynamic Farming]] | membership = 2,000 families | membership_year = 2016 | website = {{URL|www.angelicorganics.com}} }}
'''Angelic Organics''', located in [[Caledonia, Illinois]], is one of the oldest [[community-supported agriculture|Community Supported Agriculture]] (CSA) farms in the United States. Angelic Organics has grown produce in accordance with organic and [[Biodynamic agriculture|biodynamic principles]] since 1990. Participating subscribers, known as [[shareholders]], receive a weekly 3/4 bushel box of fresh vegetables and herbs delivered to over 40 [[Chicago]] area sites.
Angelic Organics was featured in the award winning documentary film ''[[The Real Dirt on Farmer John]]''.<ref name="farm1">{{cite web|url=http://angelicorganics.com/ao/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=148&Itemid=182|title=The Real Dirt on Farmer John|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=|work=Angelic Organics|accessdate=}}</ref>
