The '''Animals in Science Committee''' is an advisory [[non-departmental public body]] created by the British government in 2013 under the auspices of the [[Animals (Scientific Procedures) Act 1986]] as part of its obligation under [[European Directive 2010/63/EU]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/animals-in-science-committee/about|title=Animals in Science Committee: What We Do|publisher=GOV.UK|accessdate=2014-05-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rspca.org.uk/sciencegroup/researchanimals/ethicalreview/differentsystems/uk/committee|title=Animals in Science Committee|publisher=RSPCA|date=2014-05-15}}</ref> It replaces the previous [[Animal Procedures Committee]].
